5:
Wow... Look at this bonanza. And 
everything's for hunting dragons?
8: Yes. Would you like to learn more, Alk?
12:
What kid doesn't want to hear about 
dragons?
...Hey. Why do you have two of these 
knives?
16:
An excellent question. Now, these two 
knives may LOOK the same, but...
24:
Swing one, and the blade will ignite. 
Swing the other, and it unleashes 
a bitter frost.
25:
A dragon may be any one of the six 
elements. One requires different tools 
when skinning a water or a thunder 
dragon.
31:
However, as in any fight, knowledge is 
the keenest tool. It's like that old 
saying: if you know the enemy and 
know yourself, you need not fear the 
result of a hundred battles.
37:
But one does not learn about dragons 
overnight. It takes years of diligent 
study and observation.
42:
(How long is he going to keep 
talking...)
46:
Take this spear. It is a weapon 
I designed to be particularly effective 
against the beasts.
Go on. Try wielding it.
56:
Exactly! The weight of that spear is 
what makes it deadly.
58:
Light slashes and jab will merely 
glance off of a dragon's scales.
62:
But a heavy thrust! THAT will penetrate 
to the core!
65:
I see. I'd, uh, love to hear more, but it's 
time I got dinner going...
68:
MOST renowned dragon slayers of yore 
were spear-users. What that tells us is
—
77:
Of course! Didn't you just express your 
desire to hear more?
85:
...And that is the bare minimum any 
self-respecting warrior should know 
about dragons. Do you have any 
questions, Alk?
...ALK?!
94:
What?! The sun's set!
I'm so sorry, Alk!
96:
I tend to get a bit... over-zealous when 
it comes to dragons. It's why everyone 
calls me Dragon's Swain, instead of 
Dragon's Bane.
99: How... How can I ever atone for this?
104:
Please stop talking like you just killed 
me...
106:
Anyways, we need to eat. What are 
you feeling tonight? Meat?
110:
Meat... Yes... Alk, how would you like to 
try dragon meat?
115: Dragon meat? Is it any good?
118:
Ah! The light has been rekindled in 
your eyes!
Yes, dragon meat is known as the gem 
of all game. It is so rare and delicious, 
it is sometimes called miracle meat, 
and a good-sized cut is worth its 
weight in gold.
122:
Miracle meat... I'm liking the sound of 
that.
125:
Very well then! I shall find 
a particularly plump and succulent 
dragon, and bring back its carcass so 
we may feast on it!
130:
Awesome!
So, when should we go?
136:
Yeah, but you'll also be there, right? 
I think we'd make a good team.
139:
Yes, of course... You're right. We'll go 
together, Alk.
142:
All right! Dragon meat's on the menu, 
kids!
144:
But first, let's have a normal barbeque. 
People are going to start rioting if 
I don't get dinner on the stove.
148:
...All will be well. I'm a changed man 
now. Never again will a dragon hurt 
someone I care about.
